{{see|Demonstration}}
==English==

====Etymology====
From Latin ''[[demonstratio]]'', from verb ''[[demonstrare]]'', "show" or "explain", from prefix ''[[de-]]'', "of" or "concerning", + verb ''[[monstrare]]'', "show".

===Pronunciation===
*''UK:'' {{IPA|/demənˈstreɪʃən/}}
*{{audio|En-us-demonstration.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The act of [[demonstrate|demonstrating]]; showing or explaining something.
# An event at which something will be demonstrated.
# A public display of group [[opinion]].

====Related terms====
*[[demonstrable]]
*[[demonstrate]]
*[[demonstrator]]
*[[monster]]
*[[remonstration]]

